const pageTitle = "Dungeon Generator";
---

<PersonalBaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
	<h1> Dungeon Generator </h1>
	<p> This project is <b> still in development</b>!</p>
	<iframe frameborder="0" src="https://itch.io/embed-upload/13484487?color=ffc7ca" allowfullscreen="" width="960" height="620"><a href="https://theartofgaming.itch.io/dungeon-generator">Play Dungeon Generator on itch.io</a></iframe>
        
	<p> <br> <br> Generate a variety of dungeons with the click of a button.  While there are no options for the player, there's still a variety of layouts in resulting dungeons due to the method of procedural generation.
		<br>Hopefully can be of use to DMs, devs, and boss monsters
		<br>Done in 6 days over the course of LD 57 Extra Jam to learn more about methods of procedural generation, namely binary space partitioning. 
	</p>
        
		<h3>Known Bugs</h3>
        <p> Sometimes paths will generate outside of the rooms or not connect all the rooms to one another </p>

		<h3>Next Expected Update</h3>
		<p> Q3 2025 - fixing room connections plus a fun little extra </p>

		<script>
			import '../../scripts/menu.js'
		  </script>
	
</PersonalBaseLayout>

